The paper deals with graph theory and connectivity properties of graphs, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Yao subgraphs and disk graphs also suggests a possible categorization under data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the motivation for the study of connectivity properties in mobile networks with directional antennas suggests a possible categorization under social and information networks (cs.SI).
